This is the broadcast tree protocol running in ns-3.

1. After downloading the files go to your ns-3 installation directory.
   The installation directory contains the "ns-allinone-3.26" folder with all ns-3 files.
   (I will use my version of ns-3, 3.26 for the following guidelines, 
   other versions will appear for other versions)


2. Go to "NS-3_INSTALATION_DIRECTORY"/ns-allinone-3.26/ns-3.26/src and exchange the 
   current wifi directory for the wifi directory downloaded from this repository.

3. After this, go to "NS-3_INSTALATION_DIRECTORY"/ns-allinone-3.26/ns-3.26/scratch and copy 
   the file BroadcastTreeProtocolScenario.cc

4. To run the simulation open a terminal in NS-3_INSTALATION_DIRECTORY"/ns-allinone-3.26/ns-3.26

5.a In the terminal copy the following command:
    ./waf --run  "scratch/BroadcastTreeProtocolScenario"

5.b To run the simulation with gdb instead copy:
    ./waf --run  "scratch/BroadcastTreeProtocolScenario"  --command-template="gdb --args %s"

